# Cursor Rules

## Lessons

### User Specified Lessons
- Use the python3 venv in ./venv for executing Python tools
- Include info useful for debugging in the program output
- Read files before attempting to edit them
- For git commits with multiline messages, write the message to a file first, then use `git commit -F <filename>`, and include "[Cursor] " prefix

### Cursor Learned
- Next.js project structure includes: pages/, components/, styles/, lib/, and public/ directories
- Project uses React 19.0.0, Next.js 15.1.7, TypeScript 5.7.3, TailwindCSS 4.0.9
- Animation libraries include Framer Motion 12.4.7 and GSAP 3.12.7

